  "prompt": "How does the law define illegal money laundering activities?",
  "response": "Money laundering is generally defined as the process of making illegally-obtained money appear legal by concealing its true origin. Typical legal definitions involve three key stages:\n\n1. Placement: Introducing illegal funds into the financial system\n2. Layering: Disguising the source through complex financial transactions\n3. Integration: Accessing the money appearing legitimate\n\nSpecific criminal activities often include:\n- Hiding proceeds from drug trafficking\n- Concealing funds from tax evasion\n- Disguising money from fraud or corruption\n- Transferring illegal funds through multiple accounts\n\nMost jurisdictions have specific legal statutes criminalizing these activities, with penalties potentially including significant fines and imprisonment.",
